Interface BDDStack<E>

Type Parameters:
E - the type of elements in this stack
All Superinterfaces:
Iterable<E>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractStack, ArrayStack, ListStack
public interface BDDStack<E> extends Iterable<E>
A bounded stack is a bounded, last-in-first-out (LIFO) collection of non-null elements.

Any concrete class that implements this interface should have the following one argument constructor: 


     public MyStack(int max) throw IllegalArgumentException;
The argument max will be the capacity of the stack, and the constructor will throw an IllegalArgumentException if max <= 0.

A typical bounded stack is [e1, e2, ..., ek]:N where e1..ek are the elements of the stack from bottom to top, and N is the capacity of the stack. An iterater should traverse from e1 to ek.
